<h2><code>lgEditableColumn</code> directive</h2>

<p>
	Creates a column that displays property from the data source. The displayed value is editable (the column contains the 'edit' view).
</p>
<p class="alert alert-info">
	<strong>Note</strong> Currently the edit view always renders a text input, regardless of the actual type of the data. This will be improved in future versions.
</p>

<h3>Attributes</h3>
<table class="table table-striped">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th>Attribute</th>
			<th>Type</th>
			<th>Description</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<td>property</td>
			<td>string</td>
			<td>Name of the field to bind the column to.</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<h3>Examples</h3>
<pre highlight="html">
&lt;lg-grid model="myModel"&gt;
	&lt;lg-editable-column property="firstName"&gt;&lt;/lg-editable-column&gt;
	&lt;lg-editable-column property="lastName"&gt;&lt;/lg-editable-column&gt;
&lt;/lg-grid&gt;
</pre>